org.whispercomm.c2dm4j.async.handler
Interface AsyncHandlers

public interface AsyncHandlers

A collection of MessageFilter, ResponseHandler, and ThrowableHandler objects used to automatically handle certain responses and errors in the asynchronous flow. An instance can be created using the factory methods of AsyncHandlersFactory.

Author:
David R. Bild
See Also:
AsyncHandlersFactory, DeviceBackoffThrottle, GlobalBackoffThrottle

Method Detail

appendEnqueueFilter

void appendEnqueueFilter(MessageFilter filter)
Appends a new filter to the enqueue filter chain. These filters will be called before a message is added (or re-added) to the queue.

Parameters:
filter - the enqueue filter

appendDequeueFilter

void appendDequeueFilter(MessageFilter filter)
Appends a new filter to the dequeue filter chain. These fitlers will be called when a message is dequeued for sending, but before it is sent.

Parameters:
filter - the dequeue filter

appendResponseHandler

<T extends Response> void appendResponseHandler(ResponseType type,
                                                ResponseHandler<T> handler)
Appends a new handler to the response handler chain. The handlers will be called when a response is received from C2DM. A handler that accepts multiple types must be registered once for each type.

Parameters:
type - the type of response that the handler accepts
handler - the response handler

appendThrowableHandler

<T extends Throwable> void appendThrowableHandler(Class<? extends T> type,
                                                  ThrowableHandler<T> handler)
Appends a new handler to the throwable handler chain. The handlers will be called when an exception is thrown while processing a message or handling a response. A handler that accepts multiple types must be registered once for each type.

Parameters:
type - the type of throwable that the handler accepts
handler - the throwable handler
